title: Sidewall, 1905–15
inscribed: Printed in right selvedge: "S.A. Maxwell & Co." pattern number "2414" "GB".
description: Art nouveau / mission style. Thick bands with floral medallions and foliate stripe alternating with bands of stripes of varying sizes. Printed in greens, dark red and gold liquid mica on beige-cream ground. Printed in right selvedge: "S.A. Maxwell & Co." pattern number "2414" "GB".
